modules.description: Logs messages with specified severity levels, constructs formatted log entries, and handles error recovery with custom formatting and tagging. Works with log levels, formatted message builders, and result types for error propagation. Used to instrument application flow, capture structured error details, and ensure consistent logging during failure scenarios.

Provides functions to generate and handle Twirp service implementations from Protocol Buffers definitions, including request parsing, response serialization, and error routing. Works with protobuf-generated types, including service interfaces, request messages, and response messages. Used to build lightweight, type-safe RPC services such as a calculator that supports operations like addition and division.

Provides structured logging with severity levels, formatted message construction, and error recovery mechanisms. Supports log level filtering, custom message tagging, and result type propagation for error handling. Enables detailed application instrumentation and consistent error logging. Can log debug information, capture error details in a structured format, and recover from failures with custom error messages.
